      "id": "PopularPost336231",
      "post_content": "I like this card, as a fair and interesting card draw, quite like [Compulsive Research](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Compulsive Research)...  \nYou can always put on the bottom a couple of lands that are fermenting in your hand (something that you can't do with [Brainstorm](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Brainstorm)), like you can always discard one with Compulsive Research!   \nOr you can put a couple of cards on the top if you want to use them later, or to hide them against a discard deck.   \nI'm actually surprised that they didn't reprinted this since 6th edition, about 14 years ago! Maybe they think it's a little over the curve, like for Compulsive Research.  \n  \nAnd I like the art! Phil and Kaja Foglio are one of the most funny artist of the old days! I like sometimes a little bit of funny or cartoonish art in Magic, too bad that now they want only hyper-realistic art, most of them with a super-evident computer graphic touch...   \n  \nFor nostalgia, and for actually appreciate this card, I'd give it 4.5/5... Instead, I give it 5/5 to raise its rating ... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "leomistico",
